The paper deals with the problem of distributed detection in tree networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The presence of Byzantines introduces a security aspect, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CR). The modeling of the interaction between the FC and the attacker as a game involves game theory (cs.GT). The proposed reputation-based scheme for identifying Byzantines also involves machine learning and data analysis techniques, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
